a%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20panel%20found%20that%20the%20congresswoman%20%26quot%3Bimpermissibly%20accepted%20gifts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20asked%20her%20to%20pay%20nearly%20%243%2C000%20of%20her%20own%20money%20in%20order%20to%20close%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez's%20appearance%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-met-gala-appearance-send-message-tax-the-rich-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E2021%20Met%20Gala%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended%20up%20being%20more%20expensive%20for%20her%20than%20she%20might've%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20Ethics%20Committee%20on%20Friday%20closed%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexandria-ocasio-cortez-investigation-house-ethics-committee-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyearslong%20probe%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20New%20York%20congresswoman%20and%20whether%20she%20accepted%20improper%20gifts%20in%20connection%20with%20her%20attendance%20at%20the%20high-profile%20event%2C%20where%20she%20wore%20a%20white%20dress%20emblazoned%20with%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BTax%20the%20Rich.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fethics.house.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FCommittee-Report-20250725-Rep.-Ocasio-Cortez.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E31-page%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20panel%20said%20that%20Ocasio-Cortez%20had%20%26quot%3Bimpermissibly%20accepted%20gifts%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20that%20in%20order%20for%20the%20matter%20to%20be%20closed%2C%20she%20would%20need%20to%20pay%20nearly%20%243%2C000%20in%20personal%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20%24250%20to%20cover%20the%20attendance%20of%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%2C%20Riley%20Roberts%2C%20and%20an%20additional%20%242%2C733.28%20payment%20to%20Brother%E2%80%AFVellies%2C%20the%20business%20that%20designed%20her%20dress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20Mike%20Casca%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20she%20would%20make%20those%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Congresswoman%20appreciates%20the%20Committee%20finding%20that%20she%20made%20efforts%20to%20ensure%20her%20compliance%20with%20House%20Rules%20and%20sought%20to%20act%20consistently%20with%20her%20ethical%20requirements%20as%20a%20Member%20of%20the%20House%2C%26quot%3B%20Casca%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20accepts%20the%20ruling%20and%20will%20remedy%20the%20remaining%20amounts%2C%20as%20she's%20done%20at%20each%20step%20in%20this%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20said%20that%20Ocasio-Cortez%20had%20taken%20proactive%20steps%20to%20comply%20with%20House%20Ethics%20rules%2C%20which%20include%20strict%20guidelines%20around%20accepting%20gifts.%20She%20nonetheless%20fell%20short%2C%20though%20the%20committee%20said%20it%20had%20no%20evidence%20that%20she%20%26quot%3Bintentionally%20underpaid%20for%20any%20goods%20or%20services%20received%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20Met%20Gala.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20congresswoman's%20attempts%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20gift%20rules%20included%20arranging%20to%20rent%20the%20dress%20and%20accessories%20that%20she%20was%20provided%20with%20and%20to%20pay%20for%20other%20services%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20which%20are%20usually%20provided%20to%20Met%20Gala%20guests%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20that%20her%20fianc%C3%A9's%20attendance%20was%20an%20impermissible%20gift%20because%20he%20is%20not%20yet%20her%20spouse%2C%20and%20that%20she%20initially%20failed%20to%20pay%20the%20full%20fair%20market%20value%20for%20some%20of%20the%20items%20she%20wore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Ocasio-Cortez%20and%20Roberts%20have%20already%20paid%20a%20total%20of%20%246%2C853.75%20for%20various%20services%20they%20received%20that%20night%2C%20including%20transportation%2C%20clothing%20rental%2C%20and%20rooms%20at%20the%20Carlyle%20Hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECorrection%3A%20July%2025%20%E2%80%94%20An%20earlier%20version%20of%20this%20story%20misstated%20the%20name%20of%20Ocasio-Cortez's%20fianc%C3%A9.%20It%20is%20Riley%20Roberts%2C%20not%20Riley%20Rogers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-house-ethics-probe-closed-met-gala-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753463570000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6883b86085e81483682eb2e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-house-ethics-probe-closed-met-gala-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20committee%20found%20that%20the%20congresswoman%20%26quot%3Bimpermissibly%20accepted%20gifts%26quot%3B%20in%20connection%20with%20her%20appearance%20at%20the%202021%20Met%20Gala.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A502%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-house-ethics-probe-closed-met-gala-2025-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahindra%20Lifespaces'%20Q1%20FY26%20profit%20grows%20multiple%20times%20to%20%E2%82%B951%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753461834000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fquarterly-results%2Fmahindra-lifespaces-q1-fy26-profit-grows-multiple-times-to-rs-51-cr-125072501617_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mahindra%20Lifespaces%20reports%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20Q1%20FY26%20profit%20to%20Rs%2051%20crore%2C%20despite%20a%20significant%20drop%20in%20revenue.%20The%20company%20adds%20Rs%203%2C500%20crore%20to%20its%20development%20portfolio%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fquarterly-results%2Fmahindra-lifespaces-q1-fy26-profit-grows